      "text": [
        " اَلصَّادِقُ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ : \"إِذَا أُرِّفَتِ اَلْأُرَفُ وَ حُدَّتِ اَلْحُدُودُ فَلاَ شُفْعَةَ وَ لاَ شُفْعَةَ إِلاَّ لِشَرِيكٍ غَيْرِ مُقَاسِمٍ \"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3369 - Abu Abdullah Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) said:\n\"When the landmarks are established and the boundaries are defined, there is no preemption (shufah). And there is no preemption except for a partner who has not divided (the property).\""
        ]
      }
    },
